HEADWORD: cross-examination
<hw>cross"-ex*am`i*na"tion</hw> <pr>(kr?s"?gz-?m`?-n?"sh?n; 115)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The interrogating or questioning of
a witness by the party against whom he has been called and examined. See
<er>Examination</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[fig.]</mark> <def>close or detailed
questioning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cross-examine</ent>⟦br⟧
